&lt;p&gt;Job ID # 5210_1]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;JOB TITLE: Lead, Analytics Consultant&lt;br&gt;LOCATION: 2000 McKinney Ave., Suite 2150, Dallas, TX 75201&lt;br&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES:&lt;br&gt;Lead and participate in client-facing and internal meetings, such as scoping sessions, project kickoffs. Use&lt;br&gt;professional and expert methods for eliciting client needs, based on current practices. Work with clients to&lt;br&gt;build a vision for what their requirements could/should be in future. Apply subject matter expertise to help&lt;br&gt;clients build that future state vision. Document and gain agreement with clients around the scope of work to&lt;br&gt;be performed. Use modern collaboration tools that allow communication of expectations, progress on&lt;br&gt;timelines, and status of completion of milestones and deliverables. Develop and distribute deliverables (draft,&lt;br&gt;and final versions, of reports, analysis and dashboards) for clients, in a high quality, digital manner. Align client&lt;br&gt;needs (current, and future projected) with product, engineering and professional services team goals. Identify&lt;br&gt;problematic data/data structure and provide input on ideas to correct. Identify data management process&lt;br&gt;improvement opportunities and work with key stakeholders to develop and implement effective solutions.&lt;br&gt;Consistently and visibly document such observations in appropriate feedback systems in alignment with&lt;br&gt;engineering, and client management processes. Continuously and visibly work to standardize, automate,&lt;br&gt;improve cost to serve clients with a view to scaling the business. As a data subject matter expert (SME) assume&lt;br&gt;a key role in data stewardship, making data validation, a continuous improvement to ensure accurate&lt;br&gt;reporting. Continuously and visibly work with other data stewards to develop and follow optimal data&lt;br&gt;management and reporting practices. Develop subject expertise in the data and analytics that support Avetta&lt;br&gt;with respect to Clients, Suppliers, and Workforce. Maintains an active social presence, building an audience&lt;br&gt;that regards you as an expert in your field. Partner with other teams to participate in events that promote the&lt;br&gt;Avetta way through the use of data and analytics, and impactful storytelling. Continuously scan and research&lt;br&gt;technical and strategic options for bringing new services, new analytics forward. Suggesting and building&lt;br&gt;business case toward launching of new business services. Continuously working to improve methods, analytics,&lt;br&gt;and services. Continuously striving to help get new talent onboarded and developed quickly to improve the&lt;br&gt;practice’s ability to evolve and grow cost-effectively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;JOB REQUIREMENTS:&lt;br&gt;Minimum Education Requirements: Master’s degree in Business Analytics or Math, Computer Science,&lt;br&gt;or related.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Minimum Experience Requirements: 5+ years as Data Analyst, Business Intelligence Developer, or&lt;br&gt;Analytics Consulting role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Alternate Education Requirements: Bachelor’s degree in Business Analytics or Math, Computer&lt;br&gt;Science, or related.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Alternate Experience Requirements: 7+ years as Data Analyst, Business Intelligence Developer, or&lt;br&gt;Analytics Consulting role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Apply online at http://www.avetta.com/careers. Must include job ID # 5210-1 on the resume.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;#LI-DNI&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Avetta is building the largest global community of hiring clients and suppliers that are Ready to Work. Its unified platform streamlines compliance, prequalification, safety and performance benchmarking in a single, integrated experience. Trusted by 360,000 businesses across more than 120 countries, Avetta blends AI-driven insights and human expertise to close risk gaps and strengthen supplier reliability so projects start on time, risks are managed proactively and operations scale with certainty.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;SUMMARY:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Manager, Sales Operations partners with the Sales team to manage the business with data. This role will track sales pipeline to identity opportunities and threats, reporting and modeling, and provide key forecasting and analytical insights to drive business decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If residing within commutable distance to one of our offices, a hybrid schedule would be required (3 days in office, 2 days work from home). Remote work may be considered for those outside of commutable distance to an office.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This pivotal role requires a dynamic individual who excels in a fast-paced environment and possesses a diverse skill set to manage various operational tasks, streamline processes, and drive efficiency within the organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The sales operations manager manages support functions essential to sales force productivity. These include planning, reporting, sales process optimization, sales technology optimization, sales program implementation, and sales compensation administration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide weekly / monthly reporting and analysis related to pipeline trends, key metrics and KPIs, and support of ad hoc strategic analyses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop Gap to Goal analysis to evaluate Sales Performance to Quota, coupled with business insights/recommendations to Sales Leaders and executive leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify business process and workflow improvements to drive operational efficiency and data accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and lead cross-functional teams to implement process improvements and drive strategic initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain AI-powered agents for the sales team to automate processes, improve user adoption, increase operational efficiency, and deliver data-driven insights that support sales performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with Sales Comp design, territory planning, account assignments, quota setting and sales productivity reporting as appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;IDEAL EXPERIENCE&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;u&gt;EDUCATION &amp;amp; TRAINING:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrates immaculate attention to detail and an ability to triangulate various data sources as a validation step to accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possesses a natural intellectual and systems curiosity with respect to CRM, financial systems, and analytics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quick learner who can analyze an issue from a business, finance, and IT perspective.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly proficient at working with large amounts of data and translating to a story with recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong cross-functional and collaboration skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree required; MBA preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years’ experience in Finance, Sales Operations, Sales or a related function.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 3-5 years of proven experience in managing and leading team at the supervisory/manager level&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CRM proficiency required, preferably SFDC or MSFT Dynamics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Snowflake proficien

&lt;p&gt;Avetta is building the largest global community of hiring clients and suppliers that are Ready to Work. Its unified platform streamlines compliance, prequalification, safety and performance benchmarking in a single, integrated experience. Trusted by 360,000 businesses across more than 120 countries, Avetta blends AI-driven insights and human expertise to close risk gaps and strengthen supplier reliability so projects start on time, risks are managed proactively and operations scale with certainty.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;SUMMARY:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Marketing Operations Analyst role involves providing accurate analysis and insights to the Marketing Leadership team, challenging them to think differently and acting as a trusted advisor. Key responsibilities include developing and maintaining KPI packages to measure marketing performance, communicating actionable insights from regular reporting, and driving process improvement to enhance data integrity and reporting accuracy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If residing within commutable distance to one of our offices, a hybrid schedule would be required (3 days in office, 2 days work from home). Remote work may be considered for those outside of commutable distance to an office.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a trusted advisor to the Marketing Leadership team by proactively providing accurate analysis with insights, communicate effectively, challenging leaders to think differently and becoming their go to resource&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain KPI packages to measure marketing and lead performance. This will include, but is not limited to, evaluation of marketing campaign effectiveness, performance against targets set and return on investment. Develop thinking about what is missing from current packages to tell a complete story&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate actionable takeaways and insights from regular reporting and newly developed KPI packages, identifying the next question that will be asked and digging deeper to find root cause&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive process improvement to help manage the data output from the marketing automation tool and in CRM to improve the data integrity and reporting accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
